        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Many thanks for the specimens which will be very useful whenever a new Edition is required.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>C. Darwin</p>
                    <p> Down, Beckenham, Kent | Dec. 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>—  </p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Bailey had sent CD specimens of <hi rend="italic">Bouvardia leiantha</hi> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11162.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from W. W. Bailey, [November 1877]</ref> and n. 3). In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9500.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. vii, CD noted that the specimens sent by Bailey were clearly heterostyled, but that no difference could be detected in the size of the pollen-grains.</note>
        </div>        
            
